WHEREAS, academically, Page High School has earned recognition as one of the top-
ranked high schools in Tennessee, consistently demonstrating excellence in student
achievement, college readiness, and academic performance; and
WHEREAS, with continued growth, Page has also developed into an athletic
powerhouse, emerging as a consistent contender and winner in state championships across
multiple sports; the school's athletic programs emphasize both competitive excellence and
community pride, bringing together students, families, and alumni; and
WHEREAS, in addition to athletics and academics, Page High School has garnered
numerous artistic awards and accolades through its visual arts, theater, band and choral
programs; these achievements highlight the school's commitment to fostering creativity and
well-rounded student development, further strengthening its reputation as a comprehensive
educational institution; and
WHEREAS, Page High School balances tradition with progress; students and
staff continuously fulfil the Page mission to exemplify the Patriot Spirit by leading, learning
and serving; and
WHEREAS, through decades of change, expansion, and success, Page High School
has remained a cornerstone of its community—an institution shaped by its past and prepared
for its future; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor Page High School on the occasion of its fiftieth anniversary,
commend its administration, faculty, and staff, both past and present, for their dedication to the
highest tenets of education, and extend to them our best wishes for much continued success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
